description: Borrowed from Latin anterior (“that is before, foremost”).

definitionGroups.group: (anatomy) Nearer the forward end, especially in the front of the body; nearer the head or forepart of an animal.

entries.meaning: (botany) (of a part of a flower or leaf) Situated further away from the mainstem.
(phonetics) Pronounced with an obstruction located in front of the palato-alveolar region of the mouth, e.g. b, p, d, t.
(formal) Coming before or earlier in time or development, prior to, preceding.
